problem_statement:
Subtle bug in parsing COMMENT and HISTORY cards
When parsing COMMENT or HISTORY cards, if there is a "=" in column 9, the comment or history string is placed in the value field of the header card. If no "=" is present, the string is placed in the comment field of the header card. Placing the comment or history text in the value field is problematic, because it is then skipped when `toString()` is called on the card.

`HeaderCardParser()`  makes the following calls:

```
    HeaderCardParser(String line) throws UnclosedQuoteException, IllegalArgumentException {
        this.line = line;
        // TODO HeaderCard never calls this with a null argument, so the check below is dead code here...
        // if (line == null) {
        // throw new IllegalArgumentException("Cannot parse null string");
        // }
        parseKey();
        parseValue();
        parseComment();
    }
```

If the card is a comment style card and a "=" is in column 9, then `parseValue()` grabs everything after the "=" and places it in the `HeaderCard.value` field. The `HeaderCard.comment` field is then null.

In subsequent processing, when `HeaderCardFormatter.toString()` is called, the `appendValue()` method returns immediately if the card is a comment style card, so the value is never used. This means the the text string associated with the comment or history card is lost when merging headers or even printing the card values.

If there is no "=" in column 9, then everything works as expected.

I think a simple solution is to modify `HeaderCardParser.parseValue()` to return immediately if the card is a comment-style card.

Finally, while including a "=" in a comment style card might seem strange, as far as I can tell, there is nothing in the FITS specification to preclude this, so the cards should be parsed the same way whether a "=" is present or not.

I am happy to help fix this and submit a PR if you like.

