+    }
+
+    public void setStartTime(Integer startTime) {
+        this.startTime = startTime;
+    }
+
+    public Integer getEndTime() {
+        return endTime;
+    }
+
+    public void setEndTime(Integer endTime) {
+        this.endTime = endTime;
+    }
+
+    @ShadowSources({ "entity", "previous.endTime" })
+    public Integer startTimeSupplier() {
+        if (entity == null) {
+            return null;
+        }
+        if (previous == null) {
+            return entity.startTime + Math.abs(position - entity.position);
+        }
+        return previous.endTime + Math.abs(position - previous.position);
+    }
+
+    @ShadowSources("startTime")
+    public Integer endTimeSupplier() {
+        if (startTime == null) {
+            return null;
+        }
+        return startTime + duration;
+    }
+
+}

problem_statement:
Perform count operation instead of HashAggregate when count is requested on non-null field
### Problem Statement

```sql
CREATE TABLE mytable (
   myfield INT NOT NULL
);

EXPLAIN SELECT COUNT(*) FROM mytable;
--> Count[doc.mytable | true] (rows=1)
```

This is [optimized](<URL>)

```sql
EXPLAIN SELECT COUNT(_id) FROM mytable;
--> HashAggregate[count(_id)...

EXPLAIN SELECT COUNT(myfield) FROM mytable;
--> HashAggregate[count(myfield)]...
```

On large tables this can lead to long execution times

### Possible Solutions

Check if the field involved in [COUNT(column)](<URL>) is non-nullable then consider the operation a [COUNT(*)](<URL>)

### Considered Alternatives

```sql
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM mytable;
/*no need to filter on WHERE myfield IS NOT NULL because the field is not-nullable */;
```

